Our analysis showed that LMs are not able to obtain results at a high precision ({{2303.11082_FO0046||FO}}) for all relations equally, but LM-based knowledge covers language-related and socio-demographic relations particularly well. Furthermore, we discovered that an LM's vocabulary can limit the capability of fact prediction and we achieved significant improvements with fine-tuning and vocabulary expansion.